%N A349849 Number of transitive relations on an n-set with exactly four ordered pairs.
%H A349849 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A349849/b349849.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A349849 <a href="/index/Rec#order_09">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (9,-36,84,-126,126,-84,36,-9,1).
%F A349849 a(n) = C(n,2) + 42*C(n,3) + 375*C(n,4) + 1450*C(n,5) + 2940*C(n,6) + 3360*C(n,7) + 1680*C(n,8).
%F A349849 a(n) = (1/24)*(n^8 - 12*n^7 + 84*n^6 - 340*n^5 + 814*n^4 - 1130*n^3 + 829*n^2 - 246*n).
%e A349849 a(2) = binomial(2,2) = 1. The only transitive relation with four ordered pairs on the 2-set {1,2} is {(1,1),(1,2),(2,1),(2,2)}.
%t A349849 A349849[n_] := Total[{1, 42, 375, 1450, 2940, 3360, 1680}*Binomial[n, Range[2, 8]]];
%t A349849 Array[A349849, 30, 0] (* or *)
